Function to sample Sutherland Incidence rates to Include Uncertainty

Source: R/sample_incidence_rates.R
sample_incidence_rates.Rd

Function to sample Sutherland Incidence rates to Include Uncertainty

sample_incidence_rates(incidence_rates, population_data, samples = 100)

Arguments

incidence_rates

Incidence rates as formated by sutherland_incidence_rates
population_data

Population data as formated by sutherland_data
samples

Numeric, the number of samples to take. Defaults to 100.

Value

A list of lists. Each list contains matrices of sampled incidence rates for unvaccinated, vaccinated, tuberculin postive and inelgible populations.

Examples


sample_incidence_rates(sutherland_incidence_rates, sutherland_data, samples = 5)
